# imports
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import json

# define scraping function
def scrape_page(url):
    # make a GET request to the URL and store the response
    response = requests.get(url)
    # load the HTML content from the response
    html = response.content
    # parse the HTML content using BeautifulSoup
    soup = BeautifulSoup(html, 'html.parser')
    # get the list of questions from the page
    questions = soup.find_all(class_='question-summary')
    
    # initialize an empty list to store all the question information
    question_list = []
    # loop through each question element
    for question in questions:
        # extract the question title
        question_title = question.find(class_='question-hyperlink').text
        # extract the tags of the question
        tags = [tag.text for tag in question.find_all(class_='post-tag')]
        # extract the user name
        user_name = question.find(class_='user-details').find(class_='user-details').text
        # extract the number of votes
        votes = question.find(class_='vote-count-post').text
        # extract the number of answers
        answers = question.find(class_='status').find(class_='status').text
        # extract the number of views
        views = question.find(class_='views').text
        # extract the timestamp
        timestamp = question.find(class_='relativetime').text
        
        # create a dictionary with all the extracted information
        question_dict = {
            'question_title': question_title,
            'tags': tags,
            'user_name': user_name,
            'votes': votes,
            'answers': answers,
            'views': views,
            'timestamp': timestamp
        }
        # append the dictionary to the question list
        question_list.append(question_dict)
    
    # convert the question list to JSON format
    json_data = json.dumps(question_list)
    # print out the JSON data
    print(json_data)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    # provide the URL of the website
    url = 'https://math.stackexchange.com/questions'
    # call the scraping function
    scrape_page(url)
